#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:5
msgid "How to invoke pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:7
msgid ""
":ref:`Complete pytest command-line flags reference <command-line-flags>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:9
msgid ""
"In general, pytest is invoked with the command ``pytest`` (see below for :"
"ref:`other ways to invoke pytest <invoke-other>`). This will execute all "
"tests in all files whose names follow the form ``test_*.py`` or ``\\*_test."
"py`` in the current directory and its subdirectories. More generally, pytest "
"follows :ref:`standard test discovery rules <test discovery>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:18
msgid "Specifying which tests to run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:20
msgid ""
"Pytest supports several ways to run and select tests from the command-line "
"or from a file (see below for :ref:`reading arguments from file <args-from-"
"file>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:23
msgid "**Run tests in a module**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:25
msgid "pytest test_mod.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:29
msgid "**Run tests in a directory**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:31
msgid "pytest testing/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:35
msgid "**Run tests by keyword expressions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:37
msgid "pytest -k 'MyClass and not method'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:41
msgid ""
"This will run tests which contain names that match the given *string "
"expression* (case-insensitive), which can include Python operators that use "
"filenames, class names and function names as variables. The example above "
"will run ``TestMyClass.test_something``  but not ``TestMyClass."
"test_method_simple``. Use ``\"\"`` instead of ``''`` in expression when "
"running this on Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:48
msgid "**Run tests by collection arguments**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:50
msgid ""
"Pass the module filename relative to the working directory, followed by "
"specifiers like the class name and function name separated by ``::`` "
"characters, and parameters from parameterization enclosed in ``[]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:53
msgid "To run a specific test within a module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:55
msgid "pytest tests/test_mod.py::test_func"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:59
msgid "To run all tests in a class:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:61
msgid "pytest tests/test_mod.py::TestClass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:65
msgid "Specifying a specific test method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:67
msgid "pytest tests/test_mod.py::TestClass::test_method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:71
msgid "Specifying a specific parametrization of a test:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:73
msgid "pytest tests/test_mod.py::test_func[x1,y2]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:77
msgid "**Run tests by marker expressions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:79
msgid ""
"To run all tests which are decorated with the ``@pytest.mark.slow`` "
"decorator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:81
msgid "pytest -m slow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:86
msgid ""
"To run all tests which are decorated with the annotated ``@pytest.mark."
"slow(phase=1)`` decorator, with the ``phase`` keyword argument set to ``1``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:89
msgid "pytest -m \"slow(phase=1)\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:93
msgid "For more information see :ref:`marks <mark>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:95
msgid "**Run tests from packages**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:97
msgid "pytest --pyargs pkg.testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:101
msgid ""
"This will import ``pkg.testing`` and use its filesystem location to find and "
"run tests from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:105
msgid "**Read arguments from file**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:109
msgid "All of the above can be read from a file using the ``@`` prefix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:111
msgid "pytest @tests_to_run.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:115
msgid "where ``tests_to_run.txt`` contains an entry per line, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:117
msgid ""
"tests/test_file.py\n"
"tests/test_mod.py::test_func[x1,y2]\n"
"tests/test_mod.py::TestClass\n"
"-m slow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:124
msgid ""
"This file can also be generated using ``pytest --collect-only -q`` and "
"modified as needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:127
msgid "Getting help on version, option names, environment variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:129
msgid ""
"pytest --version   # shows where pytest was imported from\n"
"pytest --fixtures  # show available builtin function arguments\n"
"pytest -h | --help # show help on command line and config file options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:139
msgid "Profiling test execution duration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:143
msgid "To get a list of the slowest 10 test durations over 1.0s long:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:145
msgid "pytest --durations=10 --durations-min=1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:149
msgid ""
"By default, pytest will not show test durations that are too small (<0.005s) "
"unless ``-vv`` is passed on the command-line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:153
msgid "Managing loading of plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:156
msgid "Early loading plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:158
msgid ""
"You can early-load plugins (internal and external) explicitly in the command-"
"line with the :option:`-p` option::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:160
msgid "pytest -p mypluginmodule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:162
msgid "The option receives a ``name`` parameter, which can be:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:164
msgid ""
"A full module dotted name, for example ``myproject.plugins``. This dotted "
"name must be importable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:165
msgid ""
"The entry-point name of a plugin. This is the name passed to ``importlib`` "
"when the plugin is registered. For example to early-load the :pypi:`pytest-"
"cov` plugin you can use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:168
msgid "pytest -p pytest_cov"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:172
msgid "Disabling plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:174
msgid ""
"To disable loading specific plugins at invocation time, use the :option:`-p` "
"option together with the prefix ``no:``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:177
msgid ""
"Example: to disable loading the plugin ``doctest``, which is responsible for "
"executing doctest tests from text files, invoke pytest like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:180
msgid "pytest -p no:doctest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:188
msgid "Other ways of calling pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:193
msgid "Calling pytest through ``python -m pytest``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:195
msgid ""
"You can invoke testing through the Python interpreter from the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:197
msgid "python -m pytest [...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:201
msgid ""
"This is almost equivalent to invoking the command line script ``pytest "
"[...]`` directly, except that calling via ``python`` will also add the "
"current directory to ``sys.path``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:208
msgid "Calling pytest from Python code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:210
msgid "You can invoke ``pytest`` from Python code directly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:212
msgid "retcode = pytest.main()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:216
msgid ""
"this acts as if you would call \"pytest\" from the command line. It will not "
"raise :class:`SystemExit` but return the :ref:`exit code <exit-codes>` "
"instead. If you don't pass it any arguments, ``main`` reads the arguments "
"from the command line arguments of the process (:data:`sys.argv`), which may "
"be undesirable. You can pass in options and arguments explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:221
msgid "retcode = pytest.main([\"-x\", \"mytestdir\"])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:225
msgid "You can specify additional plugins to ``pytest.main``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:227
msgid ""
"# content of myinvoke.py\n"
"import sys\n"
"\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyPlugin:\n"
"    def pytest_sessionfinish(self):\n"
"        print(\"*** test run reporting finishing\")\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n"
"    sys.exit(pytest.main([\"-qq\"], plugins=[MyPlugin()]))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:243
msgid ""
"Running it will show that ``MyPlugin`` was added and its hook was invoked:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:246
msgid ""
"$ python myinvoke.py\n"
"*** test run reporting finishing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/usage.rst:254
msgid ""
"Calling ``pytest.main()`` will result in importing your tests and any "
"modules that they import. Due to the caching mechanism of python's import "
"system, making subsequent calls to ``pytest.main()`` from the same process "
"will not reflect changes to those files between the calls. For this reason, "
"making multiple calls to ``pytest.main()`` from the same process (in order "
"to re-run tests, for example) is not recommended."
msgstr ""
